name: Capricorn
description: Capricorn is the tenth astrology in the zodiac of the twelve constellations of the zodiac, originating from the constellation Capricorn, the horned goat.[1] It spans 270-300 zodiac degrees, corresponding to celestial longitude. Under the tropical zodiac, the sun transmits this area from about December 21 to January 21 of the following year,[2] and under the sidereal zodiac, the sun transmits the constellation Capricorn from about January 16 to February 16.
